x4freetext: Low  Limit  of  the  Uncertainty  of  Absolute
Calibration of Used Spectrometer.
High Limit of the Uncertainty of Absolute
Calibration of Used Spectrometer.
Irradiation Time was 5 Minuts.
. The Measurments were Began After 50 Minutes
Of End of Irradiation, Approximately. These
Measurements have Been Continued During to 7 Days.
Second Cycle of the Measurements have Been Executed
After 5 Months Approximately.
The Stack has Contained Three Aluminium and
Three  Copper  Foils.   All  Foils have Diameter 20 mm.
Thicknesses were 0.0253 (AL) And 0.1015 (CU) G/Cm**2.
-By Compiler- The Expierence of Another Authors
Witnesses, That an Irradiation of One Foil Lead Up to
Partial Lost Radioactive Products.
Authors did not Give any Information About Possible
Lost Activity.
